t-family: open-sans, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.8px;\">Eventually, O’Shaughnessy and Strauss concluded they could build a pure suspension bridge within a practical range of $25-30 million with a main span at least 4,000 feet. The construction plan still faced opposition, including litigation, from many sources. By the time most of the obstacles were cleared, the Great Depression of 1929 had begun, limiting financing options, so officials convinced voters to support $35 million in bonded indebtedness, citing the jobs that would be created for the project. However, the bonds couldn’t be sold until 1932, when San-Francisco based Bank of America agreed to buy the entire project in order to help the local economy.</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 30px 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; color: #181818; font-family: open-sans, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.8px;\">The Golden Gate Bridge officially opened on May 27, 1937, the longest bridge span in the world at the time. The first public crossing had taken place the day before, when 200,000 people walked, ran and even roller skated over the new bridge.</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 30px 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; color: #181818; font-family: open-sans, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.8px;\">With its tall towers and famous trademarked \"international orange\" paint job, the bridge quickly became a famous American landmark, and a symbol of San Francisco.</p>', 'Golden Gate Bridge is born', 'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Cras aliquam odio et augue tempus, hendrerit vestibulum ligula efficitur. In nibh purus, molestie ut ligula eu, rutrum euismod quam.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '334-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-12-02 18:04:50', '2022-12-02 18:04:50', '', 334, 'http://localhost:8080/?p=461', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
